titles: An elegy on that reverend and learned minister of the Gospel, Mr. William Jenkins: Who finish'd his testimony the 19th of January, 1684/5. in the goal of Newgate, where there are above fourscore dissenters still remaining. In a dialogue between sense and faith.
notes: Verse: "Sense. Prison! O dismal thing! What wilt thou still".
Reproduction of original in the British Library.
keywords: Jenkyn, William, 1613-1685. --  Poetry --  Early works to 1800.
